Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Regnar> T transactions are normal transactions that appear on blockchain. You can see the wallets they were sent from and to, the amount sent etc. They are just like regular KMD or BTC transactions and addresses. Z transactions use zk-SNARKS, a form of zero knowledge proofs, to hide all the information in a transaction and address. No idea who sent what amount to what address, and you cant see the balances of z addresses either (re @Cryptocries: z transaction ?)
